{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-18",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_18_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 18 - The Fall-Guy",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 9,
  "page_start_sec": 255.86,
  "page_end_sec": 496.86,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.691,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 255.86,
      "end": 257.72,
      "text": "He patted her shoulder inattentively.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 258.56,
      "end": 259.46,
      "text": "His eyes were steady",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 259.64,
      "end": 260.28,
      "text": "on Gutman's."
    },
    {
      "start": 260.4,
      "end": 264.3,
      "text": "Gutman's twinkled merrily between sheltering fat puffs."
    },
    {
      "start": 265.12,
      "end": 265.66,
      "text": "He said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 266.04,
      "end": 266.56,
      "text": "\"'Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.56,
      "end": 266.78,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.92,
      "end": 271.12,
      "text": "as to that'—and put a hand inside the breast of his coat."
    },
    {
      "start": 271.8,
      "end": 272.42,
      "text": "Cairo,"
    },
    {
      "start": 272.6,
      "end": 273.52,
      "text": "hands on thighs,"
    },
    {
      "start": 273.82,
      "end": 275.14,
      "text": "leaned forward in his chair,"
    },
    {
      "start": 275.42,
      "end": 276.24,
      "text": "breathing between"
    },
    {
      "start": 276.5,
      "end": 277.58,
      "text": "and parted soft lips."
    },
    {
      "start": 278.56,
      "end": 281.02,
      "text": "His dark eyes had the surface shine of lacquer.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 281.86,
      "end": 282.56,
      "text": "They shifted their",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 282.6,
      "end": 285.36,
      "text": "focus warily from Spade's face to Gutman's,"
    },
    {
      "start": 285.38,
      "end": 287.04,
      "text": "from Gutman's to Spade's."
    },
    {
      "start": 288.16,
      "end": 288.74,
      "text": "Gutman repeated,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 289.7,
      "end": 290.26,
      "text": "\"'Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 290.36,
      "end": 290.66,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.84,
      "end": 292.16,
      "text": "as to that,'"
    },
    {
      "start": 292.78,
      "end": 294.58,
      "text": "and took a white envelope from his pocket."
    },
    {
      "start": 295.94,
      "end": 300.46,
      "text": "Ten eyes looked at the envelope.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 301.792,
      "end": 302.32,
      "text": "Turning the envelope",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 302.54,
      "end": 303.74,
      "text": "over in his swollen hands,"
    },
    {
      "start": 304.04,
      "end": 307.26,
      "text": "Gutman studied for a thoughtful moment its blank white front"
    },
    {
      "start": 307.5,
      "end": 308.38,
      "text": "and then its back,"
    },
    {
      "start": 308.85,
      "end": 310.64,
      "text": "unsealed with the flap tucked in."
    },
    {
      "start": 311.88,
      "end": 312.76,
      "text": "He raised his head,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 312.9,
      "end": 314.08,
      "text": "smiled amiably,"
    },
    {
      "start": 314.28,
      "end": 316.36,
      "text": "and scaled the envelope at Spade's lap."
    },
    {
      "start": 317.09,
      "end": 318.34,
      "text": "The envelope,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 318.56,
      "end": 319.42,
      "text": "though not bulky,"
    },
    {
      "start": 319.64,
      "end": 320.28,
      "text": "had sufficient"
    },
    {
      "start": 320.4,
      "end": 321.48,
      "text": "weight to fly true."
    },
    {
      "start": 322.54,
      "end": 324.18,
      "text": "It struck the lower part of Spade's",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 324.18,
      "end": 325.92,
      "text": "chest and dropped down on his thighs."
    },
    {
      "start": 326.82,
      "end": 329.7,
      "text": "He picked it up deliberately and opened it deliberately,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 330.0,
      "end": 331.22,
      "text": "using both hands,"
    },
    {
      "start": 331.46,
      "end": 332.22,
      "text": "having taken"
    },
    {
      "start": 332.46,
      "end": 333.96,
      "text": "his left arm from around the girl."
    },
    {
      "start": 334.36,
      "end": 337.52,
      "text": "The contents of the envelope were thousand-dollar bills,"
    },
    {
      "start": 338.18,
      "end": 339.66,
      "text": "smooth and stiff and new."
    },
    {
      "start": 340.832,
      "end": 342.42,
      "text": "Spade took them out and counted them.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 343.34,
      "end": 344.18,
      "text": "There were ten of them.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 345.152,
      "end": 345.96,
      "text": "Spade looked up,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 345.96,
      "end": 346.34,
      "text": "smiling."
    },
    {
      "start": 346.64,
      "end": 347.42,
      "text": "He said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 347.6,
      "end": 348.14,
      "text": "mildly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 349.1,
      "end": 351.14,
      "text": "We were talking about more money than this.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 352.0,
      "end": 352.38,
      "text": "Yes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 352.38,
      "end": 352.64,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 352.72,
      "end": 353.18,
      "text": "we were,"
    },
    {
      "start": 353.38,
      "end": 354.4,
      "text": "Gutman agreed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 354.98,
      "end": 356.28,
      "text": "but we were talking then."
    },
    {
      "start": 356.52,
      "end": 358.14,
      "text": "This is actual money,"
    },
    {
      "start": 358.44,
      "end": 360.0,
      "text": "genuine coin of the realm,"
    },
    {
      "start": 360.12,
      "end": 360.32,
      "text": "sir."
    },
    {
      "start": 360.9,
      "end": 363.98,
      "text": "With a dollar of this you can buy more than ten dollars' worth of"
    },
    {
      "start": 364.22,
      "end": 364.512,
      "text": "talk.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 365.66,
      "end": 367.5,
      "text": "He shook his bulbs with silent laughter.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 368.62,
      "end": 370.34,
      "text": "Then the commotion stopped and he said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 370.5,
      "end": 370.82,
      "text": "more"
    },
    {
      "start": 370.96,
      "end": 371.3,
      "text": "seriously,"
    },
    {
      "start": 371.58,
      "end": 373.06,
      "text": "yet not altogether seriously,"
    },
    {
      "start": 374.07,
      "end": 377.216,
      "text": "\"'There are more of us to be taken care of now.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 378.14,
      "end": 378.48,
      "text": "He moved",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 378.48,
      "end": 380.66,
      "text": "his twinkling eyes and his fat head sideways"
    },
    {
      "start": 380.66,
      "end": 382.72,
      "text": "with a little jerk to indicate Cairo."
    },
    {
      "start": 382.94,
      "end": 383.04,
      "text": "\"'And,"
    },
    {
      "start": 384.38,
      "end": 384.78,
      "text": "well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 384.82,
      "end": 385.08,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 385.34,
      "end": 385.94,
      "text": "In short,"
    },
    {
      "start": 386.2,
      "end": 388.46,
      "text": "the situation has changed considerably.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 390.3,
      "end": 391.14,
      "text": "While Gutman talked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 391.648,
      "end": 393.18,
      "text": "Spader tapped the edges of the ten"
    },
    {
      "start": 393.18,
      "end": 394.84,
      "text": "bills into alignment and had returned"
    },
    {
      "start": 394.9,
      "end": 395.76,
      "text": "them to their envelope,"
    },
    {
      "start": 396.14,
      "end": 397.72,
      "text": "tucking the flap in over them."
    },
    {
      "start": 398.51,
      "end": 399.26,
      "text": "Now,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 399.44,
      "end": 400.66,
      "text": "with forearms on knees,"
    },
    {
      "start": 400.92,
      "end": 402.1,
      "text": "he sat hunched forward,"
    },
    {
      "start": 402.32,
      "end": 404.32,
      "text": "dangling the envelope from a corner"
    },
    {
      "start": 404.44,
      "end": 407.34,
      "text": "held tightly by finger and thumb down between his legs."
    },
    {
      "start": 408.16,
      "end": 411.02,
      "text": "His reply to the fat man's words was careless.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 411.66,
      "end": 412.2,
      "text": "Sure."
    },
    {
      "start": 412.6,
      "end": 413.82,
      "text": "You're together now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 414.0,
      "end": 415.52,
      "text": "but I've got the Falcon.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 416.66,
      "end": 417.52,
      "text": "Joel Cairo spoke.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 418.592,
      "end": 420.9,
      "text": "Ugly white hands grasping the arms of his chair,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 421.06,
      "end": 422.52,
      "text": "he leaned forward and said"
    },
    {
      "start": 422.64,
      "end": 422.94,
      "text": "primly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 423.1,
      "end": 424.14,
      "text": "in his high-pitched,"
    },
    {
      "start": 424.18,
      "end": 424.78,
      "text": "thin voice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 425.76,
      "end": 428.1,
      "text": "I shouldn't think it would be necessary to remind you,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 428.14,
      "end": 428.28,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 428.34,
      "end": 428.6,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 428.76,
      "end": 430.34,
      "text": "that though you may have the"
    },
    {
      "start": 430.5,
      "end": 430.68,
      "text": "Falcon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 430.88,
      "end": 432.78,
      "text": "yet we certainly have you."
    },
    {
      "start": 434.176,
      "end": 435.0,
      "text": "Spade grinned.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 436.064,
      "end": 437.76,
      "text": "I'm trying not to let that worry me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 437.88,
      "end": 438.54,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 438.98,
      "end": 440.42,
      "text": "He sat up straight,"
    },
    {
      "start": 440.8,
      "end": 441.72,
      "text": "put the envelope aside,"
    },
    {
      "start": 442.04,
      "end": 443.14,
      "text": "on the end of the sofa,"
    },
    {
      "start": 443.28,
      "end": 444.3,
      "text": "and addressed Gutman."
    },
    {
      "start": 445.64,
      "end": 447.04,
      "text": "\"'We'll come back to the money later.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 447.904,
      "end": 450.08,
      "text": "There's another thing that's got to be taken care of.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 450.82,
      "end": 452.05,
      "text": "We've got to have a fall guy.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 453.42,
      "end": 455.1,
      "text": "The fat man frowned without comprehension,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 456.02,
      "end": 458.34,
      "text": "but before he could speak Spade was explaining.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 459.54,
      "end": 461.1,
      "text": "\"'The police have got to have a victim,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 461.26,
      "end": 463.66,
      "text": "somebody they can stick for those three murders."
    },
    {
      "start": 464.54,
      "end": 465.84,
      "text": "We—' Cairo,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 465.92,
      "end": 466.94,
      "text": "speaking in a brittle,"
    },
    {
      "start": 467.04,
      "end": 467.82,
      "text": "excited voice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 467.9,
      "end": 468.58,
      "text": "interrupted him."
    },
    {
      "start": 468.7,
      "end": 468.8,
      "text": "\"'Two!"
    },
    {
      "start": 469.56,
      "end": 470.72,
      "text": "Only two murders,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 470.88,
      "end": 471.04,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 471.1,
      "end": 471.38,
      "text": "Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 471.62,
      "end": 474.14,
      "text": "Thursby undoubtedly killed your partner.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 474.86,
      "end": 475.28,
      "text": "\"'All right,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 475.28,
      "end": 476.8,
      "text": "two,' Spade growled."
    },
    {
      "start": 476.92,
      "end": 478.4,
      "text": "What difference does that make?"
    },
    {
      "start": 479.04,
      "end": 479.66,
      "text": "The point is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 479.78,
      "end": 481.5,
      "text": "we've got to feed the police some—'"
    },
    {
      "start": 482.112,
      "end": 483.2,
      "text": "Now Gutman broke in,"
    },
    {
      "start": 483.3,
      "end": 484.62,
      "text": "smiling complacently,"
    },
    {
      "start": 485.1,
      "end": 486.76,
      "text": "talking with good-humoured assurance."
    },
    {
      "start": 487.24,
      "end": 487.34,
      "text": "\"'Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 488.56,
      "end": 488.86,
      "text": "sir,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 489.08,
      "end": 490.94,
      "text": "from what I've seen and heard of you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 491.28,
      "end": 493.88,
      "text": "I don't think we'll have to bother ourselves about that."
    },
    {
      "start": 494.58,
      "end": 495.76,
      "text": "We can leave the handling of the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 495.9,
      "end": 496.38,
      "text": "police to you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 496.44,
      "end": 496.86,
      "text": "all right."
    }
  ]
}